[{"location":"#SymBoltz.jl:-linear-Einstein-Boltzmann-equation-solver","page":"SymBoltz.jl: linear Einstein-Boltzmann equation solver","title":"SymBoltz.jl: linear Einstein-Boltzmann equation solver","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"SymBoltz.jl: linear Einstein-Boltzmann equation solver","title":"SymBoltz.jl: linear Einstein-Boltzmann equation solver","text":"SymBoltz.jl is a package for solving the linearized Einstein-Boltzmann system of equations. It is designed to be simple to use, extend and integrate with the wider Julia and SciML ecosystems for scientific analysis.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Features","page":"SymBoltz.jl: linear Einstein-Boltzmann equation solver","title":"Features","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"SymBoltz.jl: linear Einstein-Boltzmann equation solver","title":"SymBoltz.jl: linear Einstein-Boltzmann equation solver","text":"Represents the Einstein-Boltzmann system symbolically and solves it numerically (using ModelingToolkit.jl).\nFacilitates development of extended models by representing each component (e.g. theory of gravity and different particle species) as modular blocks of symbolic expressions that are composed to build a custom model.\nDoes not rely on approximations (like the tight coupling, ultra-relativistic fluid and radiation streaming approximations), but solves the resulting stiff equations with implicit integrators (using DifferentialEquations.jl).\nEnables automatic differentiation of any output quantity (using ForwardDiff.jl).\n~Accelerates the solution over GPUs (using DiffEqGPU.jl).~\n~Uses the variable conventions of the seminal paper by Ma and Bertschinger (1995) in most places.~\nInteroperates with other packages from the wider Julia and SciML ecosystem for parameter fitting, sensitivity analysis, and so on.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Installation","page":"SymBoltz.jl: linear Einstein-Boltzmann equation solver","title":"Installation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"SymBoltz.jl: linear Einstein-Boltzmann equation solver","title":"SymBoltz.jl: linear Einstein-Boltzmann equation solver","text":"Launch julia, enter the package manager by hitting ] and enter (one of)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"SymBoltz.jl: linear Einstein-Boltzmann equation solver","title":"SymBoltz.jl: linear Einstein-Boltzmann equation solver","text":"add https://github.com/hersle/SymBoltz.jl # for usage\ndev https://github.com/hersle/SymBoltz.jl # for development","category":"page"},{"location":"#Usage","page":"SymBoltz.jl: linear Einstein-Boltzmann equation solver","title":"Usage","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"SymBoltz.jl: linear Einstein-Boltzmann equation solver","title":"SymBoltz.jl: linear Einstein-Boltzmann equation solver","text":"TODO: tutorials","category":"page"}]
